<HEADLINE> Elvis Birthday Celebrations Planned  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    MEMPHIS, Tenn. (AP) -- Elvis Presley would have been 65 today and to mark
the occasion his fans will get another chance to see him as a much younger man.
</P>
<P>
	   A concert with Presley performing on video with live backup musicians is
part of a birthday celebration staged by Graceland Enterprises Inc., the
business manager of his estate.
</P>
<P>
	   Graceland has taken the concert around the world since its debut in Memphis
in 1997. It is scheduled for a second European tour this spring.
</P>
<P>
	   Fan club officers hold an annual meeting in Memphis in conjunction with the
birthday, and a gospel brunch is scheduled Sunday.
</P>
<P>
	   Tonight's two-hour concert, with seating for 8,300 at the Mid-South
Coliseum, is a blend of Elvis videos on a 20-foot screen and live performances
by singers and band members who toured with him in the 1970s.
</P>
<P>
	   "Once we start, we're not following any kind of digital track. We're just
going with his voice," said Joe Guercio, the show's musical director.
</P>
<P>
	   Presley's birthday celebrations generally attract several hundred fans from
around the country and abroad. Annual gatherings on Aug. 16, the anniversary of
his 1977 death, draw much larger crowds.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
