</SUBHEAD>
<P>
	   PHOENIX (AP) -- David Robinson had 24 points and nine rebounds and Tim
Duncan had 19 points and 15 boards Friday night as the San Antonio Spurs routed
Phoenix 102-83 -- the worst loss in Scott Skiles' 11 games as coach. San
Antonio, which had lost two in a row and five of eight, built a 22-point lead in
a dominating third quarter and coasted in the fourth. The Spurs were 13-for-13
at the foul line in the third quarter, while the Suns were 0-for-2.
</P>
