<HEADLINE> Rapper Stanley Howse Pleads Innocent  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Rapper Stanley Howse of Bone Thugs-N-Harmony has pleaded
innocent to weapons charges and making a terrorist threat.
</P>
<P>
	   Howse, 26, was arrested Monday when relatives in Los Angeles called police
after an argument that apparently started when Howse arrived for a visit.
Investigators said the rapper, who entered his plea Thursday in Municipal Court,
was armed with a loaded shotgun and refused to leave the house after officers
arrived.
</P>
<P>
	   Howse, known as "Flesh Bone" with his Grammy-winning rap group, faces one
count each of possession of a gun by a convicted felon, illegal possession of a
shotgun, illegal possession of a short-barreled shotgun, making a terrorist
threat and resisting an officer. All are felony charges.
</P>
<P>
	   He pleaded guilty last year to assault with a deadly weapon in a case
triggered by a dispute with a former neighbor who complained about shots being
fired at Howse's home on July 4, 1997.
</P>
<P>
	   Howse was sentenced to three years' probation and ordered to undergo anger
management training and perform community service.
</P>
