<HEADLINE> United States 8, Czech Republic 1  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    MELBOURNE, Australia (AP) -- Top players or not, the U.S. women's team still
opened the Australia Cup with a rout.
</P>
<P>
	   In the Americans' first game since their World Cup stars began a boycott
over wages, they beat the Czech Republic 8-1 Friday in the opener of the
four-nation Australia Cup.
</P>
<P>
	   Jenny Mascaro and Sherrill Kester scored twice each for the Americans, who
used a roster of mostly college stars after their well-known players said they
wouldn't appear unless they U.S. Soccer Federation agreed to higher salaries.
</P>
<P>
	   The 18 women on the U.S. roster had combined for just one previous
international goal.
</P>
<P>
	   Mascaro opened the scoring in the 14th minute when she volleyed in a chip
from Kester, beating goalkeeper Zuzana Pincova. Susan Bush made it 2-0 in the
17th minute, and Nikki Serlenga scored in the 39th minute.
</P>
<P>
	   Kester scored in the 50th and 57th minutes for a 5-0 lead. Mascaro added her
second in the 65th minute, and second-half substitute Christie Welsh scored on a
shot from the edge of the penalty area in the 74th minute. Veronica Zepeda
scored the eighth goal in the 83rd minute.
</P>
<P>
	   Iveta Dudova scored with five minutes left for the Czechs.
</P>
<P>
	   In Sydney, Sweden beat Australia 2-0 on goals by Hanna Llungberg in the 15th
minute and Cecilia Sandell in the 26th.
</P>
<P>
	   On Monday, the U.S. team plays Sweden at Melbourne and Australia plays the
Czechs.
</P>
</TEXT>
