<HEADLINE> Two Actresses To Play Selena  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    SAN ANTONIO (AP) -- Playing slain Tejano singer Selena in a new musical will
be so demanding it will take two lead performers to keep the show going.
</P>
<P>
	   Texan Rebecca Valadez will alternate with New York-based singer Veronica
Vasquez in the title role of "Selena Forever," which debuts in San Antonio in
March before going on a 30-city tour, and ultimately on to Broadway.
</P>
<P>
	   Valadez, 21, of San Antonio was a backup singer on the 1998 Janet Jackson
tour.
</P>
<P>
	   "It feels fantastic to be a part of this," she told the San Antonio
Express-News. "I feel good about the singing and the dancing, but the acting is
new to me."
</P>
<P>
	   Director Bill Virchis said producers chose two actresses to play Selena as
an adult because of the part's physical demands.
</P>
<P>
	   "The young lady will have to sing 14, 15 songs a night, up to seven or eight
nights a week," Virchis said. "It's unheard of."
</P>
<P>
	   Vasquez, 24, is a Latin/R&AMP;B singer based in New York City.
</P>
