<HEADLINE> Bus With Kids, Truck Crash in N.M.  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   TINNIE, N.M. (AP) -- A tractor-trailer rig collided with a bus loaded with
children Saturday on U.S. Highway 70 in southern New Mexico, the sheriff's
department said.
</P>
<P>
	   A spokeswoman at the Lincoln County Medical Center in Ruidoso said the
emergency room was alerted to accept five people in critical condition. There
were no immediate reports of fatalities.
</P>
<P>
	   A sheriff's dispatcher said she did not know if the bus belonged to a church
or school. It was unknown how many children were aboard.
</P>
<P>
	   The collision occurred at Tinnie, a farming and ranching community about 200
miles south of Albuquerque.
</P>
