<HEADLINE> Bus, Truck Crash in N.M., 2 Killed  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   TINNIE, N.M. (AP) -- A tractor-trailer rig hauling produce rear-ended a
church activities van Saturday in southern New Mexico, killing two people, state
police said.
</P>
<P>
	   Both of the people who died were on the van, said state police Lt. Tim
Baughman. He said he wasn't sure how many people were in the van or whether any
of the victims were children.
</P>
<P>
	   The Lincoln County Medical Center in nearby Ruidoso had four adults in its
emergency room from the accident and was expecting two more, said Jim Gibson,
hospital administrator.
</P>
<P>
	   The Red Cross set up an emergency shelter at a church in Ruidoso for
survivors or relatives, said spokeswoman Dorothetta Ernest.
</P>
<P>
	   The collision occurred on two-lane U.S. Highway 70 at Tinnie, a farming and
ranching community in a mountainous area about 200 miles southeast of
Albuquerque.
</P>
