<HEADLINE> 4 Die in Kazakstan Dorm Fire  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MOSCOW (AP) -- Four people were killed and 16 injured on Saturday in a
dormitory fire in northeastern Kazakstan, the ITAR-Tass news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
	   Three men and a woman died of burns and asphyxiation. Some residents of the
dormitory panicked and suffered severe injuries when they jumped out the windows
of lower floors, ITAR-Tass said.
</P>
<P>
	   More than 80 people were safely evacuated from the burning building in the
town of Pavlodar, near the Russian border.
</P>
<P>
	   Investigators were trying to pinpoint the cause of the fire, which some
thought might have been caused by a burning cigarette butt.
</P>
<P>
	   No other details were available.
</P>
</TEXT>
