<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Boy, 11, Charged with Raping Girl  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MADISON, Wis. (AP) -- Prosecutors have charged an 11-year-old boy with raping
an 8-year-old girl in a relative's apartment.
</P>
<P>
	   The middle school student was charged Friday with first-degree sexual
assault of a child. Dane County Juvenile Court Commissioner Jim Olds ordered the
boy held in the juvenile jail pending a plea hearing Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
	   The boy, who has been in foster care, has five prior convictions for theft,
attempted armed robbery, damage to property and other offenses, court records
showed.
</P>
<P>
	   According to allegations filed in Juvenile Court, he was at a relative's
apartment where several children were ``playing house'' while the adult was at
work, police said.
</P>
<P>
	   The boy allegedly took the girl into a bedroom, covered her mouth with his
hand and raped her, Madison police spokesman Dave Gouran said.
</P>
<P>
	   The girl was taken the following day to Meriter Hospital, where officials
alerted police. Detectives arrested the boy at school on Thursday.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
