</P>
<SUBHEAD>
Gore, Bradley Meet in Iowa
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
	   JOHNSTON, Iowa (AP) -- Bill Bradley accused Al Gore of trying to scare Iowa
voters with misrepresentations of his health care proposal on Saturday. The vice
president said he has not been hiding in a Washington bunker but campaigning on
"the front lines in the fight for our future." Bradley got the last words in the
debate, and used them to criticize Gore on the agriculture issue, asking Iowa
farmers to ask themselves if they're "better off than you were seven years ago
or do we need a change?"
</P>
