Redskins Top Lions in NFC Wildcard Game
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
	   LANDOVER, Md. (AP) -- The Washington Redskins routed the mistake-prone
Detroit Lions 27-13 in an NFC wild-card game today. The Redskins, who led 27-0
at halftime and won their fifth in a row at home, travel to Tampa Bay for the
NFC divisional playoffs next week. Tampa Bay had a first-round bye. Washington's
Stephen Davis, playing despite a sore ankle, ran for 119 yards and two
touchdowns before suffering a sprained knee five minutes into the second
quarter.
</P>
