<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-01-08 23:28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> No. 10 Indiana 85, Penn St 78  </HEADLINE>
    By DAVID KINNEY Associated Press Writer
<TEXT>
<P>
	   STATE COLLEGE, Pa. (AP) -- Kirk Haston scored a career-high 28 points and
outplayed Jarrett Stephens, the Big Ten's top scorer, as No. 10 Indiana beat
Penn State 85-78 Saturday night for its sixth straight victory.
</P>
<P>
	   Haston, with Larry Richardson, made converted a series of layups to protect
the Hoosiers' narrow lead down the stretch. Haston added 13 rebounds.
</P>
<P>
	   A.J. Guyton had 15 points and Richardson 11 for Indiana (12-1, 2-0 Big Ten),
which shot 57 percent in defeating the Lions for a sixth straight time. Michael
Lewis had eight assists and Jeffrey Newton blocked five shots.
</P>
<P>
	   Other than a brief spurt in the second half, Stephens, the league's top
scorer with 20.2 points per game, never hurt Indiana. Though he grabbed 14
rebounds, he finished with just 14 points.
</P>
<P>
	   Joe Crispin led Penn State (8-5, 0-2) with 24 points and went 11-of-11 from
the line. Titus Ivory added 19, including two 3s with four minutes left to keep
Penn State within 76-70, but they couldn't get closer than five in the second
half.
</P>
<P>
	   Indiana went ahead 48-36 at the start of the second half -- with lots of
help from the Lions, who missed their first four shots and had four turnovers in
the first six minutes.
</P>
<P>
	   Indiana kept running its usual methodical offense: Guyton drove for a
basket, Haston found a wide-open Newton for a dunk and Newton's 10-footer
rattled in and the Hoosiers had their biggest lead of the game.
</P>
<P>
	   Then Stephens showed up -- briefly. After scoring only seven points in the
first half, Stephens took a pass from Joe Crispin inside for one basket, then
went up strong for a three-point play. Crispin's fall-away 15-footer and
coast-to-coast layup pulled the Lions within five points.
</P>
<P>
	   Over the next two minutes, Jon Crispin, Joe's brother, kept it close with
two 3s and a drive past Michael Lewis.
</P>
<P>
	   But Indiana countered time and again with in-the-paint finesse.
</P>
<P>
	   Indiana led by nine early after holding Penn State without a basket for more
than four minutes during a 14-0 run. Guyton started it with a jumper, then found
Newton inside for a dunk. Newton returned the favor, dishing the ball to Guyton
for two more. A couple of fast-break baskets later, the Hoosiers were up 20-11.
</P>
<P>
	   Penn State rallied to within 35-34, but Guyton's 3 put Indiana up six points
at halftime.
</P>
<P>
	   The Hoosiers held the Lions to 39 percent shooting.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
