<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-01-08 23:52 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Oklahoma 82, No. 13 Texas Tech 76  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    NORMAN, Okla. (AP) -- Phylesha Whaley scored 25 points in Oklahoma's 82-76
victory over No. 13 Texas Tech on Saturday night.
</P>
<P>
	   Whaley was 8-for-12 from the field and 9-for-11 from the foul line to lead
the Sooners, who shot 60.9 percent from the field as a team.
</P>
<P>
	   LaNeishea Caufield and Stacey Dales scored 15 points each for Oklahoma
(11-3), which led Texas Tech (11-2) at halftime 36-30.
</P>
<P>
	   Texas Tech had five players in double digits, led by Katrisa O'Neal's 16
points. Aleah Johnson and Plenette Pierson each had 15; Melinda Pharies 13 and
Keitha Dickerson 11.
</P>
<P>
	   Texas Tech shot only 33.3 percent of its shots in the first half, but
improved to 54.5 percent in the second half to finish 43.9 percent for the game.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
